                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works. The final two works are not sufficiently visible to determine if the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>There is no columetric layout of text</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <descDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#8r #16r #24v #35v #43v #50v #60r"/>, etc. (line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#88v #133r"/> (multiple full stops between lines of red and black dots).
                  </decoNote>
                  </descDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#68r"/>: the midpoint of the Psalms is marked with the words “and this is its half.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    The end of this codex is badly damaged and many of the pages were not separated at the time of digitization to prevent further damage
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 32
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    red string is sewn into the fore edge of <loucs target="#8"/>;
                    brown string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#16, 24, 35, 43, 50, 73, 88, 103, 126"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 does not contain the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters, but space is left to include them
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#20v #27r #35r"/>);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#64r #66r #89r #110r #128r"/>, etc.).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                  </additions>
